DataElement.preferredName: Medical Device Product Material Effective Date and Time Range ISO21090.IVL.TS.DATETIME.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An object intended for use whether alone or in combination for diagnostic, prevention, monitoring, or therapeutic purposes. EXAMPLE(S): tongue depressor, pacemaker The date and time span for when the material is active.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Medical Device Product Material Effective Date and Time Range
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any physical object that is useful for prevention, diagnosis, monitoring, or treatment of disease or other conditions.:The end result of a manufacturing process; anything that is produced.:The tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object._Existing in fact and ready for service.:An expression of both date and time that an event has happened or will happen.:The difference between the lowest and highest numerical values; the limits or scale of variation.
